Definitions (Semantic Rules)

    (01) statement*.forEach(statement -> statement.returnType = type.returnType)

Expressions (Semantic Rules)

    (01)    expression1.type = expression2.type.squareBrackets(expression3.type)
    (02)    expression1.type = expression2.type.dot(ID)
    (03)    expression1.type = expression2.type.canBeCastTo(type)
    (04)    expression1.type = expression2.type.arithmetic()
    (05)    expression1.type = expression2.type.logic()
    (06)    expression1.type = expression2.type.arithmetic(expression3.type)
    (07)    expression1.type = expression2.type.comparison(expression3.type)
    (08)    expression1.type = expression2.type.logic(expression3.type)
    (09)    expression1.type = expression2.type.parenthesis(expression*.map(e->e.type))
    (10)    expression1.type = expression2.type.modulus(expression3.type)
    (11)    expression1.type = IntType
    (12)    expression1.type = RealType
    (13)    expression1.type = CharType
    (14)    expression1.type = expression1.definition == null ? new ErrorType("Variable" + ID "was not previously defined"); expression.definition.type

Statements (Semantic Rules)
    (01)    expression.type.mustBeBuiltIn()
    (02)    expression.type.mustBeBuiltIn()
    (03)    expression2.type.mustPromoteTo(expression1.type)
    (04)    expression.type.mustBeLogical()
    (05)    expression.type.mustBeLogical()
    (06)    expression.type.mustPromoteTo(statement.returnType)
    (07)    expression.type.parenthesis(expression*.map(e->e.type))

